claude_desc: Technical terminology or domain-specific vocabulary appearing in structured contexts like code, documentation, or specialized content.
Sentence-ending periods in formal academic or technical writing, often following statements of fact, research findings, or methodological explanations.
References to properties or identifiers containing "_b" in programming code, often in the context of test methods that verify response objects and their properties.
